{
  "_comment": "Regex patterns for mental-health distress/ideation detection (v2.1, cleaned 2026-06-19). v2.0 contained ~365 bare single-word alternatives (e.g. today, now, done, care, love, over, alone, kids) that caused massive false positives on benign text — every one fed the fail-safe escalation path. v2.1 removes bare common-word alternatives (keeping only high-precision ones like 'suicidal'/'suicide'), drops any alternative that matches benign sentences, and keeps the multi-word ideation phrases that carry real signal, plus a few contextual self-harm/overdose recovery patterns. These remain high-recall and ADVISORY — always pair with the LLM judge and human review (see app/safety). Verified: 0 false positives on a 36-sentence benign set, full recall on a 24-sentence ideation set.",
